Wickham's magnificent strike doubled the lead soon after to give the scoreline a fair reflection of the home side's dominance.

It was a stunning effort from the 21-year-old, firing home from 25 yards to give keeper Antonio Adan no chance.

Elsewhere, Patrick van Aanholt continued to impress for Sunderland, with new signing Santiago Vergini also making his first appearance for the club.

But an injury to Emanuele Giaccherini, who hobbled off just before half-time, will give boss Gus Poyet something to think about. 

